      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 10 六三</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 10 六三</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>六三，眇能視，跛能履，履虎尾，咥人，凶。武人為于大君。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The third SIX, divided, shows a one-eyed man (who thinks he) can see; a lame man (who thinks he) can walk well; one who treads on the tail of a tiger and is bitten. (All this indicates) ill fortune. We have a (mere) bravo acting the part of a great ruler.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
